'''West Forsyth High School''' is a public high school, located in [[Cumming, Georgia]], a suburb northeast of [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. The school opened in 2007 and is located at 4155 Drew Road, Cumming GA 30040.<ref name="WFHS Opening">{{cite web |url=http://www.forsyth.k12.ga.us/132420212171728397/blank/browse.asp?A=383&BMDRN=2000&BCOB=0&C=78884 |title=WFHS Timeline |publisher=Forsyth County Schools|accessdate=2009-07-24}}</ref><ref name="WFHS Address">{{cite web |url=http://www.forsyth.k12.ga.us/wfhs/site/default.asp? |title=WFHS Homepage |publisher=Forsyth County Schools|accessdate=2009-07-24}}</ref> It is 1 of 5 high schools in the [[Forsyth County Schools|Forsyth County School]] District, and serves students residing in [[Cumming, Georgia]]. Its school district comprises the South-West of Forsyth County. [[Image:West Forsyth High School Main Entrance.jpg|left|thumb|The school's front entrance]]
==Athletics and Clubs== West Forsyth currently competes in Region 6-AAAAA and has since 2010.<ref name="GHSAAthletics">{{cite web |url=http://www.ghsa.net/region |title=GHSA Region Alignment |publisher=GHSA |accessdate=2009-07-24}}</ref><ref name="Georgia High School Football Historians">{{cite web |url=http://ghsfha.org/rstandings.php?gTeamID=West%20Forsyth|title=GHSFHA West Forsyth Yearly Region Standings|publisher=GHSFHA |accessdate=2009-07-24}}</ref> WFHS has 18 varsity sports teams: competition cheerleading, cross country, football, football cheerleading, softball, volleyball, basketball, basketball cheerleading, swimming, wrestling, baseball, golf, lacrosse, equestrian<ref>"Clubs/Organizations / Equestrian Team." Forsyth County Schools / Overview. 07 Sept. 2011. Web. 29 Aug. 2011. <http://www.forsyth.k12.ga.us/Page/23148></ref>, soccer, tennis, track and field, and a marching band. West Forsyth also has a Region 6-AAAAA competing theatre troupe.
== Bomb Scare == On Friday, April 23, 2010, the school had a bomb scare. Four juveniles entered the school property around 2 am and vandalized the exterior of the school with spray paint.
The suspects left obscene messages including drawings of genitalia, vulgar insults, and racist messages. A student had left a car overnight, which was vandalized and had smashed windows.
Upon arrival to school students were greeted by these images. Word spread of a bomb threat spray painted in several spots. It warned of a 10:45 bomb. Subsequently hundreds of students left the building by either being picked up by parents or leaving on their own accord (albeit without school consent). However, the school officials made no acknowledgment of the bomb threat. A couple hundred students remained in the school at 10:45. No bomb ever did go off, and none was ever found.<ref>http://www.cbsatlanta.com/news/23247318/detail.html</ref><ref>http://www.hometowntimes.com/cumminghome/news50000/news/vandalism-and-bomb-threat-at-west-forsyth-high-sch~email.shtml</ref><ref>http://wsbradio.com/localnews/2010/04/school-vandalism.html</ref>
